What is the use of trying to figure out the number of connections, etc., in the brain? We can analyze a human skeletal muscle and talk about the number of myofibrils, etc., but it is the movements of the muscles (exercises) that bring about structural changes in the muscles. In a similar manner mind-related activity brings about structural changes in the brain.



