Author::::Kerry26
DateTime::::2016-02-28T21:29:17Z
The misery (that comes as a result of various psychological situations that people experience, that result in worry, rumination, etc.) CAUSES structural changes in the brain – not the other way around! If the doctors did not give fancy labels, then there would not be any stigma either. Doctors should simply treat the symptoms of the patient (such as stress, worry, etc.) and refer to them as temporary conditions that need attention, rather than giving fancy names (labels) to various “mental illnesses” – these names have no logical basis at all.



