Author::::Kerry26
DateTime::::2016-02-28T21:16:26Z
I would like to see data that show mental illnesses are brain diseases. Misery (arising from any psychological factor) leads to rumination, worry etc., and it is well known that these mind- proliferations result in various mental issues (many studies support this). Also, rumination, worry etc., lead to structural changes in the brain (epigenetics and neuroplasticity). In other words, the changes in the mind-states CAUSED the structural changes in the brain. I really do not understand why people fail to understand this! Also, all the stigma for mental illnesses come from the fancy labels that doctors give the patients based on subjective criteria (without doing any objective tests – as I have described in my other comments below).



