Author::::Kerry26
DateTime::::2016-02-28T19:36:56Z
Doctors use a lot of authentic sounding jargon to justify their diagnosis without using any objective tests. The truth is that despite decades of research, scientists have not been able to find any structural or other brain differences between patients who are “mentally ill” and healthy individuals. This is why there are no objective tests. Also, getting a label can be devastating for most patients, leading to more depression and thinking that they are somehow different from others, ‘doomed for life’ etc. A label can also increase stigma. We also know that changes in the mind (proliferating, ruminating, worry, etc.) is a risk factor for mental illness and also bring about adverse changes in the brain (neuroplasticity).



Author::::Kerry26
DateTime::::2016-02-28T19:28:34Z
What do you mean “rubbish scientists”? If you have not heard of neuroplasticity, you can do some searches on Medline. Do a search for ‘epigenetics’ too. Investigations in epigenetics have shown that mind states bring about changes in genetic regulation. Also I just posted two links (in response to Marya62) – they show that meditation/mindfulness practises bring about healthy structural changes the brain.



Author::::Kerry26
